READY FREDDY
If you have a child who will be attending
kindergarten in the fall of 2020, join us for a
unique opportunity to prepare your child for the
transition. Families that participate will be mailed
fun activities and free books!

1. Virtual welcome from your school district!
2. Four weeks of fun activities to do with your child.
3. Four free books and online Ready Freddy story times.
4. Start kindergarten READY TO LEARN!

Ready Freddy is a program of United Way of York County,
in partnership with South Eastern School District.

Register your family by June 30!

The program kicks off July 6, 2020!

Pre-registration is required by June 30.
Register online at www.unitedway-york.org/Ready-Freddy or call Julie at 717-771-3822.

There will be NO SESD meal distribution tomorrow, Friday 5/29.

Starting next week, meal distribution will be on Mondays only throughout the month of June (6/1, 6/8, 6/15, 6/22 and 6/29). You will receive 5 breakfast meals and 5 lunch meals each Monday.

This distribution will be from 9 a.m.-12 p.m. at KD and Stewartstown Elementary only.

Families that typically pick up at Delta Peach Bottom Elementary have been contacted via email to make arrangements for them to pick up or receive delivery. If you have not responded to that email, please do so ASAP. If you did not receive an email and will have difficulty picking up at these times/dates/locations in June, please reach out to grahamk@sesd.k12.pa.us and we will try to work something out so you can continue to receive meals.

post_text:
As you may already know, the Board of Directors approved the move of the half-day, pre-kindergarten program previously located at Delta-Peach Bottom Elementary School to an all-day district wide pre-kindergarten program that will operate out of Fawn Area Elementary School beginning beginning in the Fall of the 20-21 school year.. Eligibility is based upon the following requirements:
• Reside in South Eastern School District.
• Student must be (4) years of age on or before September 1, 2020.
• Student must meet the mandated health requirements for initial entry into public school.
• Parents/guardians must meet the Pre-K Counts income eligibility requirement.
If you meet these requirements and would like to submit a PreK application for consideration, please visit the main page of the district website and open the link to begin the application process (link is also attached). Applications will be accepted through May 22, 2020.
If your application meets qualifying guidelines, we will contact you to begin the document verification process.

Eligibility is based upon the following requirements:

Mason-Dixon Community Services, Inc.
April 6 at 4:08 PM ·

Please help spread the word about our drive-through food distribution this Friday in New Park, Pennsylvania!

This service is open to any resident in the New Park/Fawn Grove area who has been financially impacted by the COVID-19 pandemic and is in need of food.

When you arrive, you will be welcomed by our staff and given further instructions on how to proceed. Please remain in your car so we can follow social distancing requirements.

If you have any questions, call the Delta office at 717-456-5559 or send an email to ahatoff@mason-dixon.org

Thank you for your help spreading the word!
